==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic: cognate with Old Frisian [[skett]] ‘money, cattle’, Old Saxon [[skat]] (Dutch [[schat]]), Old High German [[skaz]] (German [[Schatz]] ‘treasure’), Old Norse [[skattr]], Gothic [[𐍃𐌺𐌰𐍄𐍄𐍃]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ʃæat:/}}

===Noun===
'''sceatt''' (plural '''[[sceattas]]''')
# [[treasure]], [[money]], [[wealth]]
# a [[coin]] or unit of money

